<br>
Our Point raids have to be called by an officer, and at least 18 Guards have to be in attendance.  Usually Point raids are called in the prime raiding hours.<br>
<br>
As far as loot rotting.  Depends on <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>why</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> its rotting.  <br>
-If its rotting because no one wants for mains, auction it for twinks.  <br>
-If you win the bid for your twink and you are unable to run your twink there in time before it rots - you still lose the points (the risk you take).  <br>
-If no mains or twinks want but its still a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>really nice</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> item (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>like one of those SK only swords from Ssra</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->)..Offer it to a probationary/recruit for a minimum bid (<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>small set amount the class officers feel its worth</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->), and that probie has the option of starting with negative points when they become a full member.  <br>
-If its a sucky item that no one wants and its going to rot - by all means - COH someone in to loot it.<br>
<br>
There will always be some kinks in the beginning, but once you work those out - the system is a nice one imho<br>
